#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/concept/configuration.md
msgid "There are many ways to configure your application. We will focus on concepts used in the [default project template](https://github.com/yiisoft/app)."
msgstr "Ada banyak cara untuk mengonfigurasi aplikasi Anda. Kita akan fokus pada konsep yang digunakan dalam [template proyek default](https://github.com/yiisoft/app)."

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/concept/configuration.md
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Yii3 configs are part of the application. You can change many aspects of how the application works by editing configuration under `config/`."
msgid "Yii3 configs are part of the application. You can change many aspects of how the application works by editing configuration under `config/` directory."
msgstr "Konfigurasi Yii3 adalah bagian dari aplikasi. Anda dapat mengubah banyak aspek cara kerja aplikasi dengan mengedit konfigurasi di bawah `config/`."

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/concept/configuration.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Config plugin"
msgstr "Plugin konfigurasi"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/concept/configuration.md
msgid "The application template uses [yiisoft/config](https://github.com/yiisoft/config) as a composer plugin to assemble configs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/concept/configuration.md
msgid "Packages provide default configurations through defined [config groups](https://github.com/yiisoft/config#config-groups)  in the `config-plugin` key in the `extra` section of the `composer.json`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (json)
#: ../src/guide/concept/configuration.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\"extra\": {\n"
"    \"config-plugin-options\": {\n"
"        \"source-directory\": \"config\",\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"config-plugin\": {\n"
"        \"params\": \"params.php\",\n"
"        \"web\": \"web.php\"\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/concept/configuration.md
msgid "After Composer updates autoload files, such as during `dump-autoload`, `install`, `require`, `update`, or `remove`, the plugin scans installed packages for configurations and writes a merge plan to `config/.merge-plan.php`.  The merge plan declares the order of merging found configurations into the final configuration to be passed to [DI container](di-container.md)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/concept/configuration.md
msgid "At runtime, `Yiisoft\\Config\\Config` loads the defined config groups according to that merge plan.  Configs are read in three layers:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: ../src/guide/concept/configuration.md
msgid "Vendor package configs with default values."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: ../src/guide/concept/configuration.md
msgid "Root package configs from the application `config/` directory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
#: ../src/guide/concept/configuration.md
msgid "Environment-specific configs from the application."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/concept/configuration.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"> [!WARNING]\n"
"> Config keys with the same name are not allowed within a single layer.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/concept/configuration.md
msgid "The application template stores configurations in a PHP file instead of inline JSON:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (json)
#: ../src/guide/concept/configuration.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\"extra\": {\n"
"    \"config-plugin-file\": \"config/configuration.php\"\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/concept/configuration.md
msgid "That file returns the same keys you could otherwise define in `composer.json`: `config-plugin`, `config-plugin-options`, and `config-plugin-environments`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/concept/configuration.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use App\\Environment;\n"
"\n"
"return [\n"
"    'config-plugin-options' => [\n"
"        'source-directory' => 'config',\n"
"    ],\n"
"    'config-plugin' => [\n"
"        'params' => 'common/params.php',\n"
"        'params-web' => [\n"
"            '$params',\n"
"            'web/params.php',\n"
"        ],\n"
"        'params-console' => [\n"
"            '$params',\n"
"            'console/params.php',\n"
"        ],\n"
"        'bootstrap' => 'common/bootstrap.php',\n"
"        'bootstrap-web' => '$bootstrap',\n"
"        'bootstrap-console' => '$bootstrap',\n"
"        'di' => 'common/di/*.php',\n"
"        'di-web' => [\n"
"            '$di',\n"
"            'web/di/*.php',\n"
"        ],\n"
"        'di-console' => '$di',\n"
"        'di-delegates' => [],\n"
"        'di-delegates-console' => '$di-delegates',\n"
"        'di-delegates-web' => '$di-delegates',\n"
"        'di-providers' => [],\n"
"        'di-providers-web' => '$di-providers',\n"
"        'di-providers-console' => '$di-providers',\n"
"        'events' => [],\n"
"        'events-web' => '$events',\n"
"        'events-console' => '$events',\n"
"        'routes' => 'common/routes.php',\n"
"    ],\n"
"    'config-plugin-environments' => [\n"
"        Environment::DEV => [\n"
"            'params' => [\n"
"                'environments/dev/params.php',\n"
"            ],\n"
"        ],\n"
"        Environment::TEST => [\n"
"            'params' => [\n"
"                'environments/test/params.php',\n"
"            ],\n"
"        ],\n"
"        Environment::PROD => [\n"
"            'params' => [\n"
"                'environments/prod/params.php',\n"
"            ],\n"
"        ],\n"
"    ],\n"
"];\n"
msgstr ""

